  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "formula_derivation",
      "instructions": "Derive the general expression for the De Giorgi exponent (critical scaling exponent) for a dissipative PDE in dimension n where the diffusion operator is of order 2s. The exponent should relate the scaling of the velocity/scalar field to the spatial scale such that the nonlinearity and dissipation scale identically."
    },
    {
      "label": "pde_verification",
      "instructions": "For each of the following PDEs, identify the dimension n and the diffusion order 2s, then calculate the specific De Giorgi exponent using the general formula derived by the first helper: 1. 3D Navier-Stokes, 2. 2D Navier-Stokes, 3. 1D Burgers, 4. Surface Quasi-Geostrophic (SQG) equation, 5. Magnetohydrodynamics (MHD), 6. Fractional Navier-Stokes. List the (n, s) pair and the resulting exponent for each."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "Combine the general formula from the first helper with the specific values calculated in the second helper. Ensure the general formula is consistent with all six test cases provided to confirm its universality."
}

